-<DIV8 N="§  143.10" TYPE="SECTION">
-<HEAD>§  143.10   Applicability and scope.</HEAD>
-<P>(a) This subpart establishes regulations pertaining to pipes, pipe or plumbing fittings, or fixtures, solder and flux, pursuant to, <I>inter alia,</I> sections 1417 and 1461 of the Safe Drinking Water Act (42 U.S.C. 300g-6 and 300j-21). It applies to any person who introduces these products into commerce, such as manufacturers, importers, wholesalers, distributors, re-sellers, and retailers. It also applies to any person who uses these products in the installation or repair of:
-</P>
-<P>(1) A public water system; or
-</P>
-<P>(2) A residential or nonresidential facility providing water for human consumption.
-</P>
-<P>(b) Reserved.
-
-
-</P>
